{
  "text": "Multiple Sclerosis (MS) is a chronic disabling neurological disorder affecting both the white and gray matter of the central nervous system. Up to 70% of MS patients develops various degrees of cognitive impairment that can be observed since early disease phases, sometimes at clinical onset [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "25783642",
